Class Parser

  • java.lang.Object
    • Parser
  • public class Parser
extends java.lang.Object
    This class deals with making sense of the user command. The commands includes: deadline, todo, event, done, delete, find, list.

    • Method Detail

      • deadlineTasks

        public static void deadlineTasks​(java.lang.String command,
                                 TaskList tasks)
        Add a deadline task to the task list, if the user entered a deadline command. The deadline task must follow the format: deadline /by time. Print our the number of tasks on the list after adding the new task. Save the new task to the data file. If the command does not follow the format, print an error message specifying the desired format. If something went wrong when save the task to the data file, print an error message.
        Parameters:
        command - The command users entered
        tasks - The existing list of tasks
        Throws:
        java.lang.StringIndexOutOfBoundsException - If the command does not follow the correct format
        java.io.IOException - If something went wrong when save the task to the data file

      • doneTasks

        public static void doneTasks​(java.lang.String command,
                             TaskList tasks)
        Mark a specific task as done. The command must follow the format: done . Save the new task status to the data file. If the command does not follow the format, print an error message specifying the desired format. If something went wrong when save the task to the data file, print an error message.
        Parameters:
        command - The command users entered
        tasks - The existing list of tasks
        Throws:
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - If the command does not follow the correct format
        java.io.IOException - If something went wrong when save the task to the data file
        java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - If the index is not on the existing task list.
